# Component CSS optimization

Component packages must not bundle `@signozhq/tailwind-config/global.css` or `@signozhq/design-tokens`. The app loads design tokens once; components only ship minimal CSS.

## Required pattern for `packages/*/src/index.css`

1. **Do not import** `@signozhq/tailwind-config/global.css` (it pulls in full design-tokens and bloats every component bundle).

2. **Use this header** (then your component-specific rules):

```css
@import 'tailwindcss';
@source "./";

@variant dark (&:where(.dark, .dark *));
```

3. **Add only** `:root` vars that this component’s Tailwind classes actually use (e.g. `--ring`, `--destructive` for focus/aria). Omit vars used only in global.css.

4. **Keep** all component-specific rules (e.g. `[data-slot='...']`, `[data-color='...']`, etc.). They may reference design token vars like `var(--bg-vanilla-300)`; those resolve at runtime when the app has loaded global.css or design-tokens.

5. **Result**: Smaller dist CSS (no design-tokens inlined). The consuming app must import `@signozhq/tailwind-config/global.css` or `@signozhq/design-tokens/dist/style.css` once so token variables are defined.

## Reference

- Good example: `packages/badge/src/index.css` (no global.css import, uses `@source "./"`, minimal `:root`, then `[data-color]` rules).
- Bad: any `index.css` that contains `@import '@signozhq/tailwind-config/global.css';` (remove that line and apply the pattern above).
